Third-party components used, unmodified, for interoperability
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The following are NOT authored by CasCet. They are official / ecosystem
components that CasCet builds on and are subject to their own licenses:

- Cep18X402 payment token (`contracts/external/Cep18X402.wasm`)
  Reference CEP-18 token with `transfer_with_authorization` (EIP-3009) from
  make-software/casper-x402 — https://github.com/make-software/casper-x402
  Deployed to Casper Testnet only so the hosted CSPR.cloud facilitator can
  settle real x402 payments; CasCet did not author this contract.

- @make-software/casper-x402 and @x402/* — x402 middleware / client libraries.

- @modelcontextprotocol/sdk and @modelcontextprotocol/server-everything
  (used in examples/wrap-third-party to demonstrate wrapping a third-party MCP
  server) — Model Context Protocol, Anthropic.

- Odra framework and odra-modules (CEP-18 base) — https://odra.dev

- The hosted x402 facilitator at x402-facilitator.cspr.cloud (Casper / CSPR.cloud)
  is an external service CasCet calls; it is not part of this repository.
